description.description: On November 3, 2020, Georgia started reporting "Anitgen Positive Cases" which are recorded as Probable cases. The roughly 30,000 cases recorded on November 3 were from the previous months.

description.description: On November 3, 2020, Georgia started reporting probable deaths in their COVID-19 Daily Status report. On November 4, we added the probable deaths in our Deaths (probable) field for November 3 and 4, causing the daily rise in deaths on the 3rd to appear as 480. This large increase includes the data dump of 450 probable deaths, many of which are not from the most recent 24 hour period.
